Merge pull request #91 from alicoding/l10nOptimization

Optimizing L10N

Optimizing L10N

Changes to this patch and why:

1. Change from JSON to YAML
  This is just an improvement in translation flow for our translators.
Using YAML will allow us to add comments for our translators in case the
strings is unclear.

2. Added bulk require for preloading all the translation files
  This will help reduce error and runtime issue for loading our
translation files.

3. Remove namespace for pages.
  We used to namespace all of our strings, but since we are not a big
application I don't think that's useful, yet.

Switch to Universal Analytics, add Optimizely

Fix l10n issue

In Router component the expected object is
``` json
{

  locales: [...],
  messages: {...}
}
```

but I mistakenly passed only the messages object without its parents, so
this is why it failed to load the page.

I'm going to document all these l10n related stuff in another ticket and
make sure it's in the README.
